# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:69
msgid "-A-"
msgstr "-A-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:70
msgid "A-Roll:"
msgstr "A-Roll:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:71
msgid "The Principal video that is usually someone speaking."
msgstr "Glavni video koji obično prikazuje nekoga kako govori."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:72
msgid "Aliasing:"
msgstr "Aliasing:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:73
msgid ""
"The undesirable jagged or stair-stepped appearance of angled lines in an "
"image, graphic, or text."
msgstr ""
"Neželjeni nazubljeni ili stepenasti izgled koso postavljenih linija u slici, "
"grafici ili tekstu."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:74
msgid "Alpha:"
msgstr "Alfa:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:75
msgid ""
"Alpha blending is a convex combination of two colors allowing for "
"transparency effects in computer graphics.  The value of alpha in the color "
"code ranges from 0.0 to 1.0, where 0.0 represents a fully transparent color, "
"and 1.0 represents a fully opaque color."
msgstr ""
"Alfa blendanje je konveksna kombinacija dviju boja koja omogućuje efekte "
"prozirnosti u računalnoj grafici. Vrijednost alfe u kodu boje kreće se od "
"0.0 do 1.0, gdje 0.0 predstavlja potpuno prozirnu boju, a 1.0 potpuno "
"neprozirnu boju."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:76
msgid "Alpha Channel:"
msgstr "Alfa kanal:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:77
msgid ""
"An alpha channel is a channel in an image or movie clip that controls the "
"opacity region."
msgstr ""
"Alfa kanal je kanal u slici ili video isječku koji kontrolira područje "
"neprozirnosti."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:78
msgid "Ambient Noise:"
msgstr "Ambijentalna buka:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:79
msgid "Ambient noise is background noise specific to the shooting location."
msgstr "Ambijentalna buka je pozadinska buka specifična za mjesto snimanja."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:80
msgid "Animation:"
msgstr "Animacija:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:81
msgid ""
"The technique of making inanimate objects or drawings appear to move in "
"motion pictures or computer graphics."
msgstr ""
"Tehnika kojom neživi objekti ili crteži izgledaju kao da se kreću u "
"filmovima ili računalnoj grafici."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:82
msgid "Anti-Aliasing:"
msgstr "Anti-aliasing:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:83
msgid ""
"Anti-aliasing is a process for smoothing jagged lines in an image.  Anti-"
"aliasing can also mean a method of filtering out erroneous frequencies in an "
"audio signal."
msgstr ""
"Anti-aliasing je proces izravnavanja nazubljenih linija u slici. Također "
"može značiti metodu filtriranja pogrešnih frekvencija u audio signalu."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:84
msgid "Artifact:"
msgstr "Artefakt:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:85
msgid ""
"An artifact is undesired data in an image because of digital processing."
msgstr "Artefakt je neželjeni podatak u slici uzrokovan digitalnom obradom."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:86
msgid "Aspect Ratio:"
msgstr "Omjer stranica:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:87
msgid ""
"The ratio of width to height in a flat surface or 2-dimensional abstract "
"construction, such as an image, video, character, or pixel.  The standard "
"ratios for NTSC SD videos are 4:3 (or 1.33:1) and HD 16:9 (or 1.77:1).  The "
"most common aspect ratios for motion pictures are 1.85:1 and 2.35:1."
msgstr ""
"Omjer širine i visine na ravnoj površini ili dvodimenzionalnoj apstraktnoj "
"konstrukciji, poput slike, videa, znaka ili piksela. Standardni omjeri za "
"NTSC SD videozapise su 4:3 (ili 1,33:1) i HD 16:9 (ili 1,77:1). Najčešći "
"omjeri stranica za filmove su 1,85:1 i 2,35:1."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:88
msgid "ATSC:"
msgstr "ATSC:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:89
msgid ""
"ATSC is a digital broadcast standard that replaced the older analog NTSC "
"standard.  The standard covers both standard and high-definition formats."
msgstr ""
"ATSC je digitalni standard emitiranja koji je zamijenio stariji analogni "
"NTSC standard. Standard pokriva i standardne i visoke definicije formate."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:91
msgid "Audio Sample Rate:"
msgstr "Uzorak audio signala:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:91
msgid ""
"The number of samples taken per second to reproduce audio digitally.  The "
"higher the sample rate, the higher the quality of the digital audio.  A rate "
"of 44,100 samples per second produces CD-quality audio and captures the "
"range of human hearing."
msgstr ""
"Broj uzoraka uzetih u sekundi za digitalnu reprodukciju zvuka. Što je veća "
"stopa uzorkovanja, to je bolja kvaliteta digitalnog zvuka. Stopa od 44.100 "
"uzoraka u sekundi proizvodi zvuk kvalitete CD-a i obuhvaća raspon ljudskog "
"sluha."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:96
msgid "-B-"
msgstr "-B-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:97
msgid "B-roll:"
msgstr "B-roll:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:98
msgid ""
"B-roll is supplemental footage that provides supporting details and greater "
"flexibility when editing video.  Common examples include the footage used to "
"cut away from an interview or news report to help tell the story."
msgstr ""
"B-roll je dodatni snimak koji pruža potporne detalje i veću fleksibilnost "
"pri montaži videa. Uobičajeni primjeri uključuju snimke korištene za prekid "
"intervjua ili vijesti kako bi se bolje ispričala priča."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:99
msgid "Bit:"
msgstr "Bit:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:100
msgid ""
"The elementary unit for digital storage.  A BIT can be either a 1 (one) or a "
"0 (zero)."
msgstr ""
"Osnovna jedinica za digitalnu pohranu. BIT može biti ili 1 (jedan) ili 0 "
"(nula)."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:101
msgid "Bit Depth:"
msgstr "Dubina bita:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:102
msgid ""
"In digital graphics and video, bit depth indicates the number of colors an "
"image can display.  A high-contrast (no gray tones) black and white image is "
"1bit, meaning it can be off or on, black or white.  As bit depth increases, "
"more colors become available.  24-bit color allows for displays of millions "
"of colors.  Similarly, in digital audio, bit depth indicates the number of "
"bits per sample.  The higher the number, the better the sound quality."
msgstr ""
"U digitalnoj grafici i videu, dubina bita označava broj boja koje slika može "
"prikazati. Slika visoke kontrasta (bez sivih tonova) crno-bijela je 1-bitna, "
"što znači da može biti isključena ili uključena, crna ili bijela. Kako "
"dubina bita raste, dostupno je više boja. 24-bitna boja omogućuje prikaz "
"milijuna boja. Slično, u digitalnom zvuku, dubina bita označava broj bitova "
"po uzorku. Što je broj veći, to je kvaliteta zvuka bolja."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:103
msgid "Bitrate:"
msgstr "Brzina prijenosa podataka:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:104
msgid ""
"The frequency at which bits (binary digits) pass a given physical or "
"metaphorical point, measured in bps (bits per second).  For every second in "
"the video, the Bit Rate, or Data Rate, is the amount of data used each "
"second.  The bitrate, in Kilobits per second, can be variable or constant."
msgstr ""
"Učestalost kojom bitovi (binarni brojevi) prolaze kroz određenu fizičku ili "
"metaforičku točku, mjerena u bps (bitova u sekundi). Za svaku sekundu videa, "
"brzina prijenosa podataka je količina podataka korištenih u svakoj sekundi. "
"Brzina prijenosa, izražena u kilobitima u sekundi, može biti varijabilna ili "
"konstantna."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:105
msgid "Blue Screen:"
msgstr "Plavi ekran:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:106
msgid ""
"A blue screen is a blue background that the subject stands in front of that "
"the computer later replaces with another background in post-production.  See "
"also blue screen compositing and green screen."
msgstr ""
"Plavi ekran je plava pozadina ispred koje se nalazi subjekt, a koju računalo "
"kasnije zamjenjuje drugom pozadinom u postprodukciji. Vidi također plavi "
"ekran kompoziting i zeleni ekran."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:108
msgid "Blue Screen Compositing:"
msgstr "Kompoziting plavog ekrana:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:108
msgid ""
"The process of making all blue elements in an image transparent and placing "
"a different background underneath."
msgstr ""
"Proces kojim se svi plavi elementi na slici čine prozirnima i postavlja se "
"druga pozadina ispod."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:113
msgid "-C-"
msgstr "-C-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:114
msgid "Capture:"
msgstr "Snimanje:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:115
msgid ""
"The process of transferring source video from a camcorder or tape deck to a "
"computer.  If the source video is analog, the capture process converts the "
"video to digital."
msgstr ""
"Proces prijenosa izvornog videozapisa s kamkordera ili magnetofona na "
"računalo. Ako je izvorni video analogni, proces snimanja pretvara video u "
"digitalni oblik."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:116
msgid "Channel:"
msgstr "Kanal:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:117
msgid ""
"A channel is one of several grayscale components used to make up a color "
"image.  Red, green, and blue channels make up RGB images, with an optional "
"alpha channel for transparency."
msgstr ""
"Kanal je jedan od nekoliko komponenti u nijansama sive koje čine kolor "
"sliku. Crveni, zeleni i plavi kanali čine RGB slike, s opcionalnim alfa "
"kanalom za transparentnost."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:118
msgid "Chromakey:"
msgstr "Krominancija:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:119
msgid ""
"Chromakey is a method of creating transparency in a video source by "
"selecting a specific \"key color\" to create an alpha matte.  It is "
"frequently used on news programs to display weather graphics behind talent "
"and for visual effects compositing."
msgstr ""
"Krominancija je metoda stvaranja transparentnosti u video izvoru odabirom "
"specifične \"ključne boje\" za stvaranje alfa maske. Često se koristi u "
"vijestima za prikaz vremenskih grafika iza voditelja i za kompoziting "
"vizualnih efekata."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:120
msgid "Clip:"
msgstr "Isječak:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:121
msgid ""
"A digitized or captured portion of video, audio, or both.  Clips are media "
"files added to the Timeline, usually part of a more extensive recording."
msgstr ""
"Digitalizirani ili snimljeni dio videozapisa, zvuka ili oboje. Isječci su "
"medijske datoteke dodane na vremensku liniju, obično dio opširnijeg zapisa."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:122
msgid "Codec:"
msgstr "Kodek:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:123
msgid ""
"Codec is a video compression technology used to compress data in a video "
"file.  Codec stands for \"Compression Decompression.\" An example of a "
"popular codec is H.264."
msgstr ""
"Kodek je tehnologija video kompresije koja se koristi za komprimiranje "
"podataka u video datoteci. Kodek znači \"kompresija-dekompresija.\" Primjer "
"popularnog kodeka je H.264."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:124
msgid "Color Correction:"
msgstr "Ispravak boje:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:125
msgid ""
"The process of altering the color of a video, especially one shot under less "
"than ideal conditions, such as low light."
msgstr ""
"Proces mijenjanja boje videozapisa, osobito onog snimljenog u manje idealnim "
"uvjetima, poput slabog osvjetljenja."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:126
msgid "Compositing:"
msgstr "Kompoziting:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:127
msgid ""
"Construction of a composite image by combining multiple images and other "
"elements."
msgstr "Izrada složene slike kombiniranjem više slika i drugih elemenata."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:128
msgid "Coverage:"
msgstr "Pokriće:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:129
msgid ""
"Coverage is the process of shooting additional footage and camera angles to "
"cover the action in the scene.  Coverage is so that the editor has a more "
"excellent range of choices when the film reaches the post-production stage."
msgstr ""
"Pokriće je proces snimanja dodatnih kadrova i kutova kamere za pokrivanje "
"radnje u sceni. Pokriće omogućuje montažeru veći izbor prilikom "
"postprodukcije."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:130
msgid "Compression:"
msgstr "Kompresija:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:131
msgid ""
"The process of reducing data, such as in an audio or video file, into a form "
"that requires less space."
msgstr ""
"Proces smanjenja podataka, kao u audio ili video datoteci, u oblik koji "
"zahtijeva manje prostora."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:132
msgid "Crop Factor:"
msgstr "Faktor izreza:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:133
msgid ""
"Crop factor is a number (typically from 1.3-2.0) that represents the ratio "
"of a sensor's imaging area to that of a full-frame sensor.  Try multiplying "
"the focal length of your lens by your camera sensor's crop factor.  It gives "
"you the focal length for the lens/sensor combination."
msgstr ""
"Faktor izreza je broj (obično od 1,3 do 2,0) koji predstavlja omjer područja "
"senzora u odnosu na senzor punog formata. Pomnožite žarišnu duljinu "
"objektiva s faktorom izreza senzora kamere da dobijete žarišnu duljinu za "
"kombinaciju objektiva i senzora."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:134
msgid "Crawl:"
msgstr "Pomicanje teksta:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:135
msgid ""
"Crawl is a text effect where the text moves right-to-left (in the English-"
"speaking world)."
msgstr ""
"Pomicanje teksta je efekt gdje se tekst pomiče s desna na lijevo (u "
"engleskom govornom području)."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:136
msgid "Cross-fade:"
msgstr "Prelaz:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:137
msgid ""
"A cross-fade is a simultaneous fade-in of one audio or video source as "
"another fades out so that they overlap temporarily.  Also called a dissolve."
msgstr ""
"Prelaz je istovremeno pojavljivanje jednog audio ili video izvora dok drugi "
"nestaje, tako da se privremeno preklapaju. Također se naziva i otapanje."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:138
msgid "Cut:"
msgstr "Rez:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:139
msgid "A cut is an instantaneous change from one shot to another."
msgstr "Rez je trenutna promjena s jednog kadra na drugi."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:140
msgid "Cut-in (Insert Shot):"
msgstr "Umetnuti kadar (Cut-in):"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:141
msgid ""
"It is a type of shot that most often shows the objects the subject is in "
"contact with or manipulating.  Cut-in shots are correspondingly helpful to b-"
"roll because they stray from the subject for a short time."
msgstr ""
"To je vrsta kadra koja najčešće prikazuje predmete s kojima je subjekt u "
"kontaktu ili ih manipulira. Umetnuti kadrovi su korisni kao b-roll jer se na "
"kratko udaljavaju od subjekta."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:143
msgid "Cutting on Action:"
msgstr "Rezanje u akciji:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:143
msgid ""
"Cutting on action is a technique used to create a more interesting scene. "
"The concept is simple… when you cut in the middle of an action, it will "
"appear less jarring and more visual interesting."
msgstr ""
"Rezanje u akciji je tehnika koja se koristi za stvaranje zanimljivije scene. "
"Koncept je jednostavan… kada režete usred akcije, prijelaz izgleda manje "
"naglo i vizualno zanimljivije."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:148
msgid "-D-"
msgstr "-D-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:149
msgid "Data Rate:"
msgstr "Brzina prijenosa podataka:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:150
msgid ""
"The amount of data moved over time (for example, 10 MB per second).  Often "
"used to describe a hard drive's ability to retrieve and deliver information."
msgstr ""
"Količina podataka prenesenih tijekom vremena (na primjer, 10 MB u sekundi). "
"Često se koristi za opisivanje sposobnosti tvrdog diska da dohvaća i "
"isporučuje informacije."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:151
msgid "Denominator:"
msgstr "Nazivnik:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:152
msgid "The number or expression below the line in a fraction (such as 2 in ½)."
msgstr "Broj ili izraz ispod crte u razlomku (kao 2 u ½)."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:153
msgid "Digital Video:"
msgstr "Digitalni video:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:154
msgid ""
"Digital video is an electronic representation of moving visual images "
"(video) in the form of encoded digital data.  In contrast, analog video "
"represents moving visual images with analog signals.  Digital video "
"comprises a series of digital images displayed in rapid succession."
msgstr ""
"Digitalni video je elektronička reprezentacija pokretnih vizualnih slika "
"(video) u obliku kodiranih digitalnih podataka. Za razliku od toga, analogni "
"video prikazuje pokretne slike pomoću analognih signala. Digitalni video "
"sastoji se od niza digitalnih slika prikazanih u brzom slijedu."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:155
msgid "Digitize:"
msgstr "Digitalizirati:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:156
msgid "To convert analog video or audio to digital form."
msgstr "Pretvoriti analogni video ili audio u digitalni oblik."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:158
msgid "Dissolve:"
msgstr "Otapanje:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:158
msgid ""
"Dissolve is an image transition effect where one picture gradually "
"disappears as another appears.  Also called a cross-fade."
msgstr ""
"Otapanje je efekt prijelaza slike gdje jedna slika postupno nestaje dok se "
"druga pojavljuje. Također se naziva prelaz."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:163
msgid "-E-"
msgstr "-E-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:164
msgid "Editing:"
msgstr "Montaža:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:165
msgid ""
"Editing is the process or result of selectively sequencing video and audio "
"clips into a new video file.  Typically involves reviewing raw footage and "
"transferring desired segments from source footage into a new predetermined "
"sequence."
msgstr ""
"Montaža je proces ili rezultat selektivnog slaganja video i audio isječaka u "
"novu video datoteku. Obično uključuje pregled sirovog materijala i prijenos "
"željenih segmenata iz izvornog materijala u novu unaprijed određenu sekvencu."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:166
msgid "Effect:"
msgstr "Efekt:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:167
msgid ""
"Synthetic sounds and animations created in the digital domain applied to a "
"clip to change a specific parameter of video or audio.  Examples: the color "
"of a visual element or the reverb on an audio track."
msgstr ""
"Sintetički zvukovi i animacije stvoreni u digitalnom području primijenjeni "
"na isječak za promjenu određenog parametra videa ili zvuka. Primjeri: boja "
"vizualnog elementa ili odjek na audio zapisu."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:168
msgid "Encode:"
msgstr "Kodirati:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:169
msgid ""
"To merge the individual video signals (for example, red, green, and blue) "
"into a combined signal, or to convert a video file to a different format "
"using a codec."
msgstr ""
"Spojiti pojedinačne videosignale (na primjer, crveni, zeleni i plavi) u "
"kombinirani signal ili pretvoriti video datoteku u drugi format koristeći "
"kodek."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:171
msgid "Export:"
msgstr "Izvoz:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:171
msgid ""
"Export refers to the process of assembling your edited video project into a "
"single file that then plays back on its own, shared, or uploaded."
msgstr ""
"Exportiranje se odnosi na proces sastavljanja vašeg uređivanog video "
"projekta u jednu datoteku koja se potom može samostalno reproducirati, "
"dijeliti ili učitati."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:176
msgid "-F-"
msgstr "-F-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:177
msgid "Fade:"
msgstr "Prijelaz:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:178
msgid ""
"A fade is the gradual diminishing or heightening of visual or audio "
"intensity.  Usage: fade-out, fade to black, fade-in, or fade up from black."
msgstr ""
"Prijelaz je postupno smanjenje ili povećanje vizualne ili audio intenziteta. "
"Primjeri: zatamnjivanje, prijelaz u crno, pojavljivanje ili pojačavanje iz "
"crnog."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:179
msgid "Fade-in:"
msgstr "Pojavljivanje:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:180
msgid ""
"1.(n.) a shot that begins in total darkness and gradually lightens to full "
"brightness.  2. (v.) To gradually bring sound from inaudibility to the "
"required volume."
msgstr ""
"1. (imenica) kadar koji počinje u potpunoj tami i postupno se osvjetljava do "
"pune svjetline. 2. (glagol) postupno pojačavanje zvuka od nečujnosti do "
"željene glasnoće."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:181
msgid "Fade-out:"
msgstr "Zatamnjivanje:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:182
msgid ""
"1.(n.) a shot that begins in full brightness and gradually dims to total "
"darkness.  2. (v.) To gradually bring sound from the required volume to "
"inaudibility."
msgstr ""
"1. (imenica) kadar koji počinje u punoj svjetlini i postupno se zatamnjuje "
"do potpune tame. 2. (glagol) postupno smanjenje zvuka od željene glasnoće do "
"nečujnosti."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:183
msgid "Filter:"
msgstr "Filter:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:184
msgid ""
"A video filter is a software component that performs some operation on a "
"multimedia stream.  Multiple filters used in a chain, known as a filter "
"graph, are the process in which each filter receives input from its upstream "
"filter.  The filter graph processes the input and outputs the processed "
"video to its downstream filter."
msgstr ""
"Video filter je softverska komponenta koja izvodi neku operaciju na "
"multimedijskom toku. Više filtera korištenih u lancu, poznatom kao graf "
"filtera, proces je u kojem svaki filter prima ulaz od prethodnog filtera. "
"Graf filtera obrađuje ulaz i šalje obrađeni video sljedećem filteru."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:185
msgid "Final Cut:"
msgstr "Finalni rez:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:186
msgid ""
"The final video production, assembled from high-quality clips, and ready for "
"export to the selected delivery media."
msgstr ""
"Završna video produkcija, sastavljena od visokokvalitetnih isječaka, spremna "
"za izvoz na odabrani medij isporuke."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:187
msgid "Finishing:"
msgstr "Završna obrada:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:188
msgid ""
"The stage that brings together all assets of a piece.  Your output from this "
"stage is your master/sub-master."
msgstr ""
"Faza koja okuplja sve elemente djela. Izlaz iz ove faze je vaš glavni ili "
"pod-glavni zapis."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:189
msgid "Footage:"
msgstr "Snimka:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:190
msgid ""
"Derived from having feet of film, this is almost synonymous with video clips."
msgstr "Izvedeno iz mjere 'feet' filma, gotovo je sinonim za video isječke."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:191
msgid "Frame:"
msgstr "Sličica:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:192
msgid ""
"In filmmaking, video production, animation, and related fields, a frame is "
"one of the many still images which compose the complete moving picture."
msgstr ""
"U filmskoj produkciji, video produkciji, animaciji i srodnim područjima, "
"sličica je jedna od mnogih statičnih slika koje čine cjelokupnu pokretnu "
"sliku."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:193
msgid "Frames Per Second (fps):"
msgstr "Sličica u sekundi (fps):"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:194
msgid ""
"The number of frames played every second.  At 15 fps and lower, the human "
"eye can detect individual frames, causing the video to appear jerky."
msgstr ""
"Broj sličica koje se prikazuju svake sekunde. Pri 15 fps i niže, ljudsko oko "
"može uočiti pojedinačne sličice, što uzrokuje trzanje videa."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:195
msgid "Frame Rate:"
msgstr "Brzina sličica:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:196
msgid ""
"Frame rate (expressed in frames per second or FPS) is the frequency (rate "
"expressed in Hz) at which consecutive images called frames appear on "
"display.  The term applies equally to film and video cameras, computer "
"graphics, and motion capture systems.  Common Frame Rate Examples: 24, 25, "
"29.97, 30, 50, 60."
msgstr ""
"Brzina sličica (izražena u sličicama u sekundi ili FPS) je frekvencija "
"(stopa izražena u Hz) kojom se na zaslonu pojavljuju uzastopne slike zvane "
"sličice. Pojam se jednako odnosi na filmske i video kamere, računalnu "
"grafiku i sustave za snimanje pokreta. Uobičajeni primjeri brzine sličica: "
"24, 25, 29.97, 30, 50, 60."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:198
msgid "Frequency:"
msgstr "Frekvencija:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:198
msgid ""
"The number of audio cycles per second, expressed in hertz (Hz).  Frequency "
"determines the pitch of a sound."
msgstr ""
"Broj audio ciklusa u sekundi, izražen u hercima (Hz). Frekvencija određuje "
"visinu tona zvuka."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:203
msgid "-G-"
msgstr "-G-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:204
msgid "Gamma:"
msgstr "Gama:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:205
msgid ""
"A measurement of the intensity of mid-tones in an image.  Adjusting the "
"gamma adjusts the level of the mid-tones while leaving the blacks and whites "
"untouched."
msgstr ""
"Mjerenje intenziteta srednjih tonova na slici. Podešavanje gamme mijenja "
"razinu srednjih tonova, dok crne i bijele tonove ostavlja nepromijenjenima."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:206
msgid "GPU:"
msgstr "GPU:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:207
msgid ""
"Graphics processing unit.  A microprocessor with built-in capabilities for "
"handling 3D graphics more efficiently than a CPU (central processing unit)."
msgstr ""
"Grafički procesor. Mikroprocesor s ugrađenim mogućnostima za učinkovitije "
"rukovanje 3D grafikom nego CPU (centralna procesorska jedinica)."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:208
msgid "Gravity:"
msgstr "Gravitacija:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:209
msgid ""
"Gravity in OpenShot is a property of each clip that sets the clip's initial "
"position on the screen."
msgstr ""
"Gravitacija u OpenShot-u je svojstvo svakog isječka koje postavlja početni "
"položaj isječka na zaslonu."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:210
msgid "Green screen"
msgstr "Zeleni ekran"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:211
msgid ""
"A green background that the subject stands in front of that is another "
"background in post-production."
msgstr ""
"Zelena pozadina ispred koje se nalazi subjekt, a koja se u postprodukciji "
"zamjenjuje drugom pozadinom."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:213
msgid "Green Screen Compositing"
msgstr "Kompozicija zelenog ekrana"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:213
msgid ""
"The process of making all green elements in an image transparent and placing "
"a different background underneath, so it appears that the subject is in a "
"different location."
msgstr ""
"Proces kojim se svi zeleni elementi na slici čine prozirnima i postavlja "
"druga pozadina ispod, tako da izgleda kao da je subjekt na drugoj lokaciji."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:218
msgid "-H-"
msgstr "-H-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:219
msgid "High Definition (HD):"
msgstr "Visoka rezolucija (HD):"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:220
msgid ""
"A general term for a video signal with a significantly higher resolution "
"than standard definition."
msgstr ""
"Opći pojam za video signal sa znatno višom rezolucijom od standardne "
"definicije."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:221
msgid "HDMI:"
msgstr "HDMI:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:222
msgid ""
"High Definition Multimedia Interface.  Interface for transmitting high "
"definition digital audio and video data."
msgstr ""
"Sučelje za multimediju visoke rezolucije. Sučelje za prijenos digitalnih "
"audio i video podataka visoke rezolucije."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:223
msgid "HDR:"
msgstr "HDR:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:224
msgid ""
"HDR (high dynamic range) is the compositing of two images, one that "
"correctly exposes the highlights, and another that properly exposes the dark "
"areas.  When composited together, you get a properly exposed image."
msgstr ""
"HDR (visoki dinamički raspon) je kompozicija dviju slika, jedne koja "
"pravilno eksponira svijetle dijelove, i druge koja pravilno eksponira tamne "
"dijelove. Kada se spoje, dobiva se pravilno eksponirana slika."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:225
msgid "HDTV:"
msgstr "HDTV:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:226
msgid ""
"High Definition TV.  A broadcast format that allows for a higher resolution "
"signal than the traditional formats, NTSC, PAL, and SECAM."
msgstr ""
"Televizija visoke rezolucije. Format emitiranja koji omogućuje signal veće "
"rezolucije od tradicionalnih formata NTSC, PAL i SECAM."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:227
msgid "HDV:"
msgstr "HDV:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:228
msgid ""
"High Definition Video.  The format used to record HDTV-quality data with "
"video camcorders."
msgstr ""
"Video visoke rezolucije. Format koji se koristi za snimanje podataka "
"kvalitete HDTV-a video kamerama."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:229
msgid "Headroom:"
msgstr "Prostor iznad glave:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:230
msgid ""
"The space between the top of a character's head and the top of the frame."
msgstr "Prostor između vrha glave lika i vrha kadra."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:231
msgid "Hiss:"
msgstr "Šum:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:232
msgid "Noise caused by imperfections in the recording medium."
msgstr "Šum uzrokovan nepravilnostima u snimnom mediju."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:234
msgid "Hue:"
msgstr "Nijansa:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:234
msgid ""
"The shade of a color.  This is the general color category into which the "
"color falls.  For example, pink, crimson, and plum are different colors, but "
"they all fall under the hue of red.  White, black, and gray tones are not "
"hues."
msgstr ""
"Odstin boje. To je opća kategorija boje u koju boja spada. Na primjer, "
"ružičasta, grimizna i šljiva su različite boje, ali sve spadaju pod nijansu "
"crvene. Bijele, crne i sive nijanse nisu nijanse boje."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:239
msgid "-I-"
msgstr "-I-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:240
msgid "Image Stabilizer:"
msgstr "Stabilizator slike:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:241
msgid ""
"Also referred to as an electronic image stabilizer.  A technique used to "
"remove the movement caused by camera shake."
msgstr ""
"Također poznat kao elektronički stabilizator slike. Tehnika koja se koristi "
"za uklanjanje pokreta uzrokovanog podrhtavanjem kamere."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:242
msgid "Importing:"
msgstr "Uvoz:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:243
msgid ""
"Importing is the process of transferring videos from your camera onto your "
"computer or into a piece of editing software."
msgstr ""
"Uvoz je proces prijenosa videozapisa s kamere na računalo ili u uređivački "
"softver."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:244
msgid "Interframe Compression:"
msgstr "Međufrejmska kompresija:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:245
msgid ""
"A compression scheme, such as MPEG that reduces the amount of video "
"information by storing only the differences between a frame and those "
"preceding it."
msgstr ""
"Shema kompresije, poput MPEG-a, koja smanjuje količinu video informacija "
"pohranjivanjem samo razlika između jednog kadra i prethodnih."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:246
msgid "Interpolation:"
msgstr "Interpolacija:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:247
msgid ""
"Used in animation to calculate the motion in between two user-generated "
"keyframes so that the editor does not need to animate each frame manually.  "
"This speeds up the process and makes the resulting animation smoother."
msgstr ""
"Koristi se u animaciji za izračunavanje pokreta između dvaju korisnički "
"definiranih ključnih kadrova kako uređivač ne bi morao ručno animirati svaki "
"kadar. To ubrzava proces i čini animaciju glađom."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:249
msgid "Intertitles:"
msgstr "Međunaslovi:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:249
msgid ""
"Titles that appear on their own between footage.  Commonly seen in silent "
"movies to substitute dialogue, also used as chapter headings."
msgstr ""
"Naslovi koji se pojavljuju sami između snimaka. Često se koriste u nijemim "
"filmovima kao zamjena za dijalog, također se koriste kao naslovi poglavlja."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:254
msgid "-J-"
msgstr "-J-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:255
msgid "J-Cut:"
msgstr "J-rez:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:256
msgid ""
"An edit in which the audio starts before the video, giving the video a "
"dramatic introduction.  Also known as an audio lead."
msgstr ""
"Rez u kojem zvuk počinje prije videa, dajući videu dramatičan uvod. Također "
"poznat kao audio predvodnik."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:257
msgid "Jog"
msgstr "Pomicanje"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:258
msgid ""
"To move forward or backward through video by playing it one field or frame "
"at a time."
msgstr ""
"Pomicanje naprijed ili nazad kroz video reprodukcijom po jedno polje ili "
"kadar."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:260
msgid "Jump Cut:"
msgstr "Preskakanje reza:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:260
msgid ""
"A jump cut is an unnatural, abrupt switch between shots identical in the "
"subject but slightly different in screen location, so the subject appears to "
"jump from one screen location to another."
msgstr ""
"Preskakanje reza je neprirodna, nagla promjena između snimaka s istim "
"subjektom, ali malo različitim položajem na ekranu, zbog čega subjekt "
"izgleda kao da skače s jednog mjesta na drugo."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:265
msgid "-K-"
msgstr "-K-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:266
msgid "Key:"
msgstr "Ključ:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:267
msgid ""
"A method for creating transparency, such as a bluescreen key or a chroma key."
msgstr ""
"Metoda za stvaranje prozirnosti, poput bluescreen ključa ili kromatskog "
"ključa."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:269
msgid "Keyframe:"
msgstr "Ključni kadar:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:269
msgid ""
"A keyframe is a frame that contains a record of specific settings (e.g., "
"scale, rotation, brightness).  Start and endpoints for animated effects.  By "
"setting multiple keyframes, you can adjust these parameters as the video "
"plays to animate certain aspects."
msgstr ""
"Ključni kadar je kadar koji sadrži zapis specifičnih postavki (npr. "
"skaliranje, rotacija, svjetlina). Početne i završne točke za animirane "
"efekte. Postavljanjem više ključnih kadrova možete prilagođavati ove "
"parametre tijekom reprodukcije videa kako biste animirali određene aspekte."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:274
msgid "-L-"
msgstr "-L-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:275
msgid "L-Cut:"
msgstr "L-rez:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:276
msgid ""
"An L-cut is an edit in which the video ends before the audio.  L-cuts act as "
"a subtle transition from one scene to the next."
msgstr ""
"L-rez je rez u kojem video završava prije zvuka. L-rezovi služe kao suptilan "
"prijelaz iz jedne scene u drugu."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:277
msgid "Letterbox:"
msgstr "Letterbox:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:278
msgid ""
"A technique used to preserve the original aspect ratio of a motion picture "
"when played on a TV.  Letterboxing adds black bars to the top and bottom of "
"the screen."
msgstr ""
"Tehnika koja se koristi za očuvanje izvornog omjera slike filma prilikom "
"prikaza na televizoru. Letterboxing dodaje crne trake na vrh i dno ekrana."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:279
msgid "Linear Editing:"
msgstr "Linearno uređivanje:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:280
msgid ""
"A form of video editing which lays out cuts sequentially, one by one, to "
"produce the final scene. This contrasts with non-linear editing which allows "
"cutting in any order."
msgstr ""
"Oblik video uređivanja koji postavlja rezove sekvencijalno, jedan po jedan, "
"kako bi se proizvela konačna scena. Suprotno je nelinearnom uređivanju koje "
"dopušta rezanje u bilo kojem redoslijedu."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:281
msgid "Log:"
msgstr "Dnevnik:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:282
msgid ""
"A record of start and end timecode, reel numbers, scene descriptions, and "
"other information for a specified clip."
msgstr ""
"Zapis početnog i završnog vremenskog koda, brojeva role, opisa scena i "
"drugih informacija za određeni isječak."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:283
msgid "Lossless:"
msgstr "Bez gubitaka:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:284
msgid ""
"A compression scheme that results in no loss of data from decompressing the "
"file.  Lossless files are generally quite large (but still smaller than "
"uncompressed versions) and sometimes require considerable processing power "
"to decode the data."
msgstr ""
"Shema kompresije koja ne gubi podatke prilikom dekompresije datoteke. "
"Datoteke bez gubitaka su obično prilično velike (ali i dalje manje od "
"nekomprimiranih verzija) i ponekad zahtijevaju znatnu procesorsku snagu za "
"dekodiranje podataka."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:286
msgid "Lossy:"
msgstr "S gubitkom:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:286
msgid ""
"Lossy compression is a compression scheme that degrades quality.  Lossy "
"algorithms compress digital data by eliminating the data least sensitive to "
"the human eye and offer the highest compression rates available."
msgstr ""
"Kompresija s gubitkom je shema kompresije koja smanjuje kvalitetu. Algoritmi "
"s gubitkom komprimiraju digitalne podatke uklanjajući one dijelove najmanje "
"osjetljive ljudskom oku i nude najviše dostupne stope kompresije."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:291
msgid "-M-"
msgstr "-M-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:292
msgid "Mark In:"
msgstr "Označi početak:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:293
msgid "Placing a marker at the beginning of where you want your clip to start."
msgstr ""
"Postavljanje oznake na početak mjesta gdje želite da vaš isječak počne."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:294
msgid "Mark Out:"
msgstr "Označi kraj:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:295
msgid "Placing a marker at the beginning of where you want your clip to end."
msgstr ""
"Postavljanje oznake na početak mjesta gdje želite da vaš isječak završi."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:296
msgid "Match Action:"
msgstr "Uskladi akciju:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:297
msgid ""
"Match action (or match cut) is a technique where an editor will cut from one "
"visually similar scene to another."
msgstr ""
"Uskladi akciju (ili usklađeni rez) je tehnika u kojoj uređivač reže s jedne "
"vizualno slične scene na drugu."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:298
msgid "Memory Bank:"
msgstr "Banku memorije:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:299
msgid ""
"A Memory Bank is a video that documents specific periods or events in "
"someone's life.  It can be set to music, make use of natural sound, record "
"vacations, or just capture moments in everyday life."
msgstr ""
"Banku memorije je video koji dokumentira određene periode ili događaje u "
"nečijem životu. Može biti popraćen glazbom, koristiti prirodne zvukove, "
"snimati praznike ili jednostavno bilježiti trenutke iz svakodnevnog života."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:300
msgid "Marker:"
msgstr "Oznaka:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:301
msgid ""
"An object used to mark a location.  Clip markers signify essential points "
"within a clip.  Timeline markers indicate scenes, locations for titles, or "
"other significant points within an entire movie.  Use clip markers and "
"timeline markers for positioning and trimming clips."
msgstr ""
"Objekt koji se koristi za označavanje lokacije. Oznake isječaka označavaju "
"važne točke unutar isječka. Oznake vremenske linije označavaju scene, mjesta "
"za naslove ili druge značajne točke unutar cijelog filma. Koristite oznake "
"isječaka i vremenske linije za pozicioniranje i rezanje isječaka."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:302
msgid "Mask:"
msgstr "Maska:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:303
msgid ""
"The transparent area of an image, typically defined by a graphic shape or a "
"bluescreen background.  Also called a matte."
msgstr ""
"Prozirno područje slike, obično definirano grafičkim oblikom ili pozadinom "
"bluescreena. Također se naziva mat."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:304
msgid "Matte:"
msgstr "Mat"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:305
msgid ""
"Matte is an image mask used in visual effects to control applying an effect "
"to certain parts of the image."
msgstr ""
"Matte je maska slike koja se koristi u vizualnim efektima za kontrolu "
"primjene efekta na određene dijelove slike."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:306
msgid "Montage:"
msgstr "Montaža:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:307
msgid ""
"A montage is a self-contained sequence of shots assembled in juxtaposition "
"to each other to communicate an idea or mood.  The implied relationship "
"between seemingly unrelated material creates a new message."
msgstr ""
"Montaža je samostalni niz kadrova složenih jedan uz drugi kako bi prenijeli "
"ideju ili raspoloženje. Implicitni odnos između naizgled nepovezanog "
"materijala stvara novu poruku."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:309
msgid "Motion Artifact:"
msgstr "Pokretni artefakt:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:309
msgid ""
"Visual interference caused by the difference between the frame rate of the "
"camera and the motion of the object.  The most common display of this is "
"when filming a computer or television screen.  The screen flickers or a line "
"scans down it, which is the difference in frame rates and a lack of "
"synchronization between the camera and television."
msgstr ""
"Vizualna smetnja uzrokovana razlikom između brzine kadrova kamere i pokreta "
"objekta. Najčešći prikaz ovoga je prilikom snimanja računala ili "
"televizijskog ekrana. Ekran treperi ili se niz linija pomiče po njemu, što "
"je posljedica razlike u brzini kadrova i nedostatka sinkronizacije između "
"kamere i televizora."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:314
msgid "-N-"
msgstr "-N-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:315
msgid "Noise:"
msgstr "Šum:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:316
msgid "Undesired data in a video or audio signal.  See also artifact."
msgstr "Neželjeni podaci u video ili audio signalu. Vidi također artefakt."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:317
msgid "Non-linear Editing:"
msgstr "Nelinearno uređivanje:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:318
msgid ""
"An editing system that performs edits at any time, in any order.  Access is "
"random, which means that the system can jump to specific pieces of data "
"without having to look through the whole footage to find it."
msgstr ""
"Sustav uređivanja koji omogućuje uređivanje u bilo kojem trenutku, bilo "
"kojim redoslijedom. Pristup je nasumičan, što znači da sustav može skočiti "
"na određene dijelove podataka bez potrebe za pregledavanjem cijelog "
"materijala."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:319
msgid "Numerator:"
msgstr "Brojnik:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:320
msgid "The number or expression above the line in a fraction (such as 1 in ½)."
msgstr "Broj ili izraz iznad crte u razlomku (kao 1 u ½)."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:322
msgid "NTSC:"
msgstr "NTSC:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:322
msgid ""
"NTSC is an abbreviation for National Television Standards Committee.  NTSC "
"is the group that initially developed the black & white and subsequently "
"color television system.  The United States, Japan, and many other countries "
"use NTSC.  Five-hundred twenty-five interlaced lines make up NTSC that "
"display at a rate of 29.97 frames per second.  ATSC Has now superseded by "
"NTSC."
msgstr ""
"NTSC je kratica za National Television Standards Committee. NTSC je grupa "
"koja je prvotno razvila crno-bijeli, a potom i kolor televizijski sustav. "
"Sjedinjene Države, Japan i mnoge druge zemlje koriste NTSC. NTSC se sastoji "
"od 525 isprepletenih linija koje se prikazuju brzinom od 29,97 kadrova u "
"sekundi. ATSC je sada zamijenio NTSC."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:327
msgid "-O-"
msgstr "-O-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:328
msgid "Offline Editing:"
msgstr "Offline uređivanje:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:329
msgid ""
"Editing a rough cut using low-quality clips, and then producing the final "
"cut with high-quality clips, usually on a more sophisticated editing system "
"than that used for developing the rough."
msgstr ""
"Uređivanje grube verzije koristeći isječke niske kvalitete, a zatim "
"proizvodnja finalne verzije s isječcima visoke kvalitete, obično na "
"sofisticiranijem uređivačkom sustavu nego onaj korišten za izradu grube "
"verzije."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:330
msgid "Online Editing:"
msgstr "Online uređivanje:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:331
msgid ""
"Doing all editing (including the rough cut) on the same clips that produce "
"the final cut."
msgstr ""
"Obavljanje cijelog uređivanja (uključujući grubu verziju) na istim isječcima "
"koji proizvode finalnu verziju."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:333
msgid "Opacity:"
msgstr "Neprozirnost:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:333
msgid ""
"An inverse measure of the level of transparency in an image, which is of "
"importance when compositing.  An image's alpha channel stores its opacity "
"information."
msgstr ""
"Obrnuta mjera razine prozirnosti u slici, što je važno pri kompoziciji. Alfa "
"kanal slike pohranjuje informacije o neprozirnosti."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:338
msgid "-P-"
msgstr "-P-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:339
msgid "PAL:"
msgstr "PAL:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:340
msgid ""
"PAL is an abbreviation for Phase Alternate Line.  This is the video format "
"standard used in many European countries.  Six-hundred twenty-five lines "
"make up a PAL picture that displays at a rate of 25 frames per second."
msgstr ""
"PAL je kratica za Phase Alternate Line. To je standard video formata koji se "
"koristi u mnogim europskim zemljama. PAL sliku čini 625 linija koje se "
"prikazuju brzinom od 25 kadrova u sekundi."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:341
msgid "Pan:"
msgstr "Panoramski pomak:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:342
msgid "A horizontal movement of the camera on a fixed axis."
msgstr "Horizontalni pomak kamere oko fiksne osi."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:343
msgid "Pan and Scan:"
msgstr "Panoramski pomak i skeniranje:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:344
msgid ""
"A method of converting widescreen images to a 4:3 aspect ratio.  Cropping "
"the video so that it fills the entire screen and panning it into position "
"shows the essential parts of the scene."
msgstr ""
"Metoda pretvaranja širokog zaslona u omjer 4:3. Obrezivanje videa tako da "
"ispuni cijeli zaslon i pomicanje u poziciju koja prikazuje bitne dijelove "
"scene."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:345
msgid "Picture in Picture (PIP):"
msgstr "Slika u slici (PIP):"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:346
msgid ""
"An effect of superimposing a small window of footage over a larger window "
"and the two play at the same time."
msgstr ""
"Efekt preklapanja malog prozora snimke preko većeg prozora pri čemu se oba "
"istovremeno reproduciraju."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:347
msgid "Pixel:"
msgstr "Piksel:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:348
msgid ""
"One of the tiny dots that make up the representation of an image in a "
"computer's memory.  The smallest unit of a digital image."
msgstr ""
"Jedna od sitnih točkica koje čine prikaz slike u memoriji računala. Najmanja "
"jedinica digitalne slike."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:349
msgid "Pixel Aspect Ratio:"
msgstr "Omjer piksela:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:350
msgid ""
"Aspect ratio is the ratio between the width and height of your video; the "
"Pixel Aspect Ratio is the ratio between the width and height of the pixels.  "
"A standard Pixel Aspect Ratio is 1:1."
msgstr ""
"Omjer slike je odnos između širine i visine vašeg videa; omjer piksela je "
"odnos između širine i visine piksela. Standardni omjer piksela je 1:1."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:351
msgid "Pixelation:"
msgstr "Pikselizacija:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:352
msgid ""
"The display of large, blocky pixels in an image caused by over-enlarging it."
msgstr ""
"Prikaz velikih, blokovitih piksela u slici uzrokovan prevelikim povećanjem."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:353
msgid "Playhead:"
msgstr "Pokazivač reprodukcije:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:354
msgid ""
"When editing audio or video in a current computer, the Playhead is a graphic "
"line in the Timeline that represents the current accessed position, or "
"frame, of the material."
msgstr ""
"Prilikom uređivanja zvuka ili videa na računalu, pokazivač reprodukcije je "
"grafička linija u vremenskoj traci koja predstavlja trenutno pristupljenu "
"poziciju ili kadar materijala."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:355
msgid "Post-production (Post):"
msgstr "Postprodukcija (Post):"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:356
msgid ""
"Post-production (post) is any video production activity following the "
"initial recording.  Typically, post involves editing, the addition of "
"background music, voice-over, sound effects, titles, and various visual "
"effects resulting in completed production."
msgstr ""
"Postprodukcija je bilo koja aktivnost u video produkciji nakon početnog "
"snimanja. Obično uključuje uređivanje, dodavanje pozadinske glazbe, "
"naracije, zvučnih efekata, naslova i raznih vizualnih efekata koji "
"rezultiraju dovršenim proizvodom."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:357
msgid "Poster Frame:"
msgstr "Poster kadar:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:358
msgid ""
"A single frame of a clip, selected as a thumbnail to indicate the clip's "
"contents."
msgstr ""
"Pojedinačni kadar isječka, odabran kao sličica koja označava sadržaj isječka."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:360
msgid "Project:"
msgstr "Projekt:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:360
msgid ""
"A project is all the files, transitions, effects, and animations that you "
"make or use within OpenShot."
msgstr ""
"Projekt obuhvaća sve datoteke, prijelaze, efekte i animacije koje napravite "
"ili koristite unutar OpenShota."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:365
msgid "-R-"
msgstr "-R-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:366
msgid "Raw Footage:"
msgstr "Sirovi materijal:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:367
msgid "Raw footage is pre-edited footage, usually direct from the camera."
msgstr "Sirovi materijal je neuređeni snimak, obično izravno s kamere."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:368
msgid "Real-time:"
msgstr "U stvarnom vremenu:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:369
msgid ""
"Real-time occurs immediately, without delay for rendering.  If a transition "
"occurs in real-time, there is no waiting, the computer creates the effect or "
"transition on-the-fly, showing it the results immediately."
msgstr ""
"Stvarno vrijeme događa se odmah, bez kašnjenja za renderiranje. Ako prijelaz "
"nastupi u stvarnom vremenu, nema čekanja, računalo stvara efekt ili prijelaz "
"u hodu, odmah prikazujući rezultate."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:370
msgid "Rendering:"
msgstr "Renderiranje:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:371
msgid ""
"The process by which the video editing software and hardware convert the raw "
"video, effects, transitions, and filters into a new continuous video file."
msgstr ""
"Proces kojim softver i hardver za uređivanje videa pretvaraju sirovi video, "
"efekte, prijelaze i filtre u novu kontinuiranu video datoteku."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:372
msgid "Render Time:"
msgstr "Vrijeme renderiranja:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:373
msgid ""
"The render time is the time it takes an editing computer to composite source "
"elements and commands into a single video file.  Rendering allows the "
"sequence, including titles and transition effects, to play in full motion."
msgstr ""
"Vrijeme renderiranja je vrijeme koje računalo za uređivanje treba da sastavi "
"izvore i naredbe u jednu video datoteku. Renderiranje omogućuje da se "
"sekvenca, uključujući naslove i efekte prijelaza, reproducira u punom "
"pokretu."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:374
msgid "Resolution:"
msgstr "Rezolucija:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:375
msgid ""
"Resolution refers to the actual number of horizontal and vertical pixels "
"your video contains.  Common resolution Examples: (SD) 640×480, (HD) "
"854x480, (HD) 1280×720, (FHD) 1920×1080, (QHD) 2560x1440, (UHD) 3840x2160, "
"and (FUHD) 7680x4320.  Often the numbers that appear vertically refer to the "
"resolution.  The examples listed would appear as SD, 480p, 720p, 1080p, "
"1440p, 4K and 8K, respectively."
msgstr ""
"Rezolucija se odnosi na stvarni broj horizontalnih i vertikalnih piksela "
"koje vaš video sadrži. Uobičajeni primjeri rezolucije: (SD) 640×480, (HD) "
"854x480, (HD) 1280×720, (FHD) 1920×1080, (QHD) 2560x1440, (UHD) 3840x2160 i "
"(FUHD) 7680x4320. Često brojevi koji se pojavljuju vertikalno odnose se na "
"rezoluciju. Navedeni primjeri pojavljuju se kao SD, 480p, 720p, 1080p, "
"1440p, 4K i 8K, redom."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:376
msgid "RGB:"
msgstr "RGB:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:377
msgid ""
"Monitors, cameras, and digital projectors use the primary colors of light "
"(Red, Green, and Blue) to make images."
msgstr ""
"Monitori, kamere i digitalni projektori koriste osnovne boje svjetla "
"(crvenu, zelenu i plavu) za stvaranje slika."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:378
msgid "RGBA:"
msgstr "RGBA:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:379
msgid ""
"A file containing an RGB image plus an alpha channel for transparency "
"information."
msgstr ""
"Datoteka koja sadrži RGB sliku plus alfa kanal za informacije o prozirnosti."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:380
msgid "Roll:"
msgstr "Roll:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:381
msgid ""
"Roll is a text effect commonly seen in end credits, where text typically "
"moves from the bottom to the top of the screen."
msgstr ""
"Roll je tekstualni efekt često viđen u završnim titlovima, gdje se tekst "
"obično pomiče od dna prema vrhu zaslona."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:383
msgid "Rough cut:"
msgstr "Grubi rez:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:383
msgid ""
"A rough cut is a preliminary edit of footage in the approximate sequence, "
"length, and content of a finished program."
msgstr ""
"Grubi rez je preliminarna montaža snimke u približnom redoslijedu, duljini i "
"sadržaju gotovog programa."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:388
msgid "-S-"
msgstr "-S-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:389
msgid "Sample Rate:"
msgstr "Uzorak po sekundi:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:390
msgid ""
"In digital audio, the number of samples per second.  The higher the number, "
"the better the sound quality."
msgstr ""
"U digitalnom zvuku, broj uzoraka po sekundi. Što je broj veći, to je "
"kvaliteta zvuka bolja."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:391
msgid "Scene:"
msgstr "Scena:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:392
msgid "Action that occurs in one location at one time."
msgstr "Radnja koja se događa na jednom mjestu u jednom trenutku."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:393
msgid "Scrub:"
msgstr "Scrub:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:394
msgid ""
"Scrubbing is an act of moving the cursor or playhead across the Timeline "
"manually.  Once specific to audio tracks, the term now also refers to video "
"tracks."
msgstr ""
"Scrubbing je čin ručnog pomicanja kursora ili pokazivača reprodukcije preko "
"vremenske linije. Nekada specifično za audio zapise, sada se pojam odnosi i "
"na video zapise."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:395
msgid "Shot:"
msgstr "Udarac:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:396
msgid "A recording of a single take."
msgstr "Snimka jednog kadra."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:397
msgid "Side Data:"
msgstr "Pomoćni podaci:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:398
msgid ""
"Auxiliary per-stream metadata (e.g. rotation, stereo3D, spherical) attached "
"to packets or streams in containers like MP4."
msgstr ""
"Pomoćni metapodaci po streamu (npr. rotacija, stereo3D, sferični) pridruženi "
"paketima ili streamovima u kontejnerima poput MP4."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:399
msgid "Slow-motion:"
msgstr "Usporeni prikaz:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:400
msgid ""
"A shot in which action takes place at a slower than average speed.  The "
"camera achieves slow-motion by speeding up the frame rate during recording "
"and then playing back the frames at a slower speed."
msgstr ""
"Kadar u kojem se radnja odvija sporije od prosječne brzine. Kamera postiže "
"usporeni prikaz povećanjem broja sličica tijekom snimanja, a zatim "
"reprodukcijom sličica sporijom brzinom."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:401
msgid "Snap:"
msgstr "Poravnanje:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:402
msgid ""
"Snapping quickly positions an object in alignment with grid lines, "
"guidelines, or another object.  Snapping causes the object to automatically "
"jump to an exact position when the user drags it to the proximity of the "
"desired location."
msgstr ""
"Poravnanje brzo postavlja objekt u skladu s mrežnim linijama, smjernicama "
"ili drugim objektom. Poravnanje uzrokuje da objekt automatski skoči na točnu "
"poziciju kada ga korisnik povuče u blizinu željene lokacije."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:403
msgid "Spherical Video:"
msgstr "Sferični video:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:404
msgid ""
"A full-sphere (360×180°) video format that requires special metadata (SV3D) "
"so players know to render it as an interactive panorama."
msgstr ""
"Video format pune sfere (360×180°) koji zahtijeva posebne metapodatke (SV3D) "
"kako bi reproduktori znali prikazati ga kao interaktivnu panoramu."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:405
msgid "Splice:"
msgstr "Spoj:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:406
msgid ""
"The process of physically attaching two pieces of film using tape or cement."
msgstr "Proces fizičkog spajanja dva komada filma pomoću trake ili ljepila."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:407
msgid "Split cut (L-cut or J-cut):"
msgstr "Podijeljeni rez (L-rez ili J-rez):"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:408
msgid ""
"An edit in which the audio starts before or after the picture cut.  Used for "
"easing the transition from one scene or shot to another."
msgstr ""
"Montaža u kojoj zvuk počinje prije ili poslije rezanja slike. Koristi se za "
"olakšavanje prijelaza s jedne scene ili kadra na drugi."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:409
msgid "Splitscreen:"
msgstr "Podijeljeni zaslon:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:410
msgid ""
"A unique effect that displays two or more scenes simultaneously on different "
"parts of the screen."
msgstr ""
"Jedinstveni efekt koji istovremeno prikazuje dvije ili više scena na "
"različitim dijelovima zaslona."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:411
msgid "Sound Effects:"
msgstr "Zvučni efekti:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:412
msgid ""
"Sound effects are contrived audio, usually prerecorded, incorporated with a "
"video soundtrack to resemble a real occurrence.  Blowing on a microphone, "
"for example, might simulate wind to accompany hurricane images."
msgstr ""
"Zvučni efekti su umjetno stvoreni zvukovi, obično unaprijed snimljeni, "
"ugrađeni u zvučni zapis videa kako bi oponašali stvarni događaj. Na primjer, "
"puhanje u mikrofon može simulirati vjetar koji prati slike uragana."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:413
msgid "Soundtrack:"
msgstr "Zvukovna podloga:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:414
msgid ""
"The soundtrack is the audio portion of a video recording, often multifaceted "
"with natural sound, voiceovers, background music, or other sounds."
msgstr ""
"Zvukovna podloga je audio dio video snimke, često višeslojna s prirodnim "
"zvukom, glasovnim komentarima, pozadinskom glazbom ili drugim zvukovima."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:415
msgid "Stabilization:"
msgstr "Stabilizacija:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:416
msgid ""
"Image stabilization is a family of techniques that reduce blurring "
"associated with the motion of a camera or other imaging device during "
"exposure."
msgstr ""
"Stabilizacija slike je skup tehnika koje smanjuju zamućenje povezano s "
"pokretom kamere ili drugog uređaja za snimanje tijekom ekspozicije."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:417
msgid "Standard Definition (SD):"
msgstr "Standardna definicija (SD):"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:418
msgid ""
"Television broadcasting standard with a lower resolution than high "
"definition."
msgstr ""
"Standard televizijskog emitiranja s nižom rezolucijom od visoke definicije."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:419
msgid "Step:"
msgstr "Korak:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:420
msgid ""
"The act of moving forward or backward through video one frame at a time."
msgstr "Radnja pomicanja naprijed ili nazad kroz video po jedan kadar."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:421
msgid "Still Frame:"
msgstr "Statični kadar:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:422
msgid "A single frame of video is repeated, so it appears to have no motion."
msgstr ""
"Pojedinačni kadar videa se ponavlja, tako da izgleda kao da nema pokreta."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:423
msgid "Straight Cut:"
msgstr "Ravni rez:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:424
msgid ""
"The most common edit, consecutive clips placed one after another in the "
"Timeline window.  Straight cuts are preferable to transitions when the "
"scenes are similar, and you do not want edits to be noticeable."
msgstr ""
"Najčešća montaža, uzastopni isječci postavljeni jedan za drugim u prozoru "
"vremenske linije. Ravni rezovi su poželjniji od prijelaza kada su scene "
"slične i ne želite da se montaže primijete."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:425
msgid "Superimposing:"
msgstr "Preklapanje:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:426
msgid "Combining images, where one or more layers involve transparency."
msgstr "Spajanje slika, gdje jedan ili više slojeva uključuje prozirnost."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:427
msgid "Sync (Synchronization):"
msgstr "Sinkronizacija (Sinhronizacija):"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:428
msgid ""
"Synchronization refers to the relative timing of audio (sound) and video "
"(image) parts during creation, post-production (mixing), transmission, "
"reception, and play-back processing."
msgstr ""
"Sinkronizacija se odnosi na relativno usklađivanje vremena audio (zvuk) i "
"video (slika) dijelova tijekom stvaranja, postprodukcije (miksanja), "
"prijenosa, prijema i reprodukcije."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:429
msgid "SECAM:"
msgstr "SECAM:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:430
msgid ""
"Systeme Electronique Couleur Avec Memoire, a TV format used mainly in "
"Eastern Europe, Russia, and Africa."
msgstr ""
"Systeme Electronique Couleur Avec Memoire, TV format koji se uglavnom "
"koristi u Istočnoj Europi, Rusiji i Africi."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:432
msgid "SV3D (Spherical Video metadata):"
msgstr "SV3D (Sferični video metapodaci):"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:432
msgid ""
"The “sv3d” atom in MP4/MOV files—side-data that marks a clip as 360° and "
"carries projection, yaw/pitch/roll parameters."
msgstr ""
"“sv3d” atom u MP4/MOV datotekama — dodatni podaci koji označavaju isječak "
"kao 360° i sadrže parametre projekcije, yaw/pitch/roll."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:437
msgid "-T-"
msgstr "-T-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:438
msgid "Tilt:"
msgstr "Nagib:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:439
msgid ""
"Tilting is a cinematographic technique in which the camera stays in a fixed "
"position but rotates up/down in a vertical plane."
msgstr ""
"Nagib je kinematografska tehnika u kojoj kamera ostaje na fiksnoj poziciji, "
"ali se rotira gore/dolje u vertikalnoj ravnini."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:440
msgid "Timecode:"
msgstr "Vremenski kod:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:441
msgid ""
"The timecode is the discrete address given to each frame of the video (for "
"example, 1:20:24:09).  Timecode makes frame-accurate editing possible and "
"allows editors to identify scenes precisely in a log."
msgstr ""
"Vremenski kod je diskretna oznaka dodijeljena svakom okviru videa (na "
"primjer, 1:20:24:09). Vremenski kod omogućuje preciznu montažu po okvirima i "
"omogućava montažerima da točno identificiraju scene u zapisu."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:442
msgid "Time-lapse:"
msgstr "Time-lapse:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:443
msgid ""
"It is a technique for capturing each frame in a video at a much slower rate "
"than usual.  When played back at regular speed, time appears to go by "
"faster.  An editing program achieves this by fast-forwarding or increasing "
"the speed of your video."
msgstr ""
"Tehnika snimanja svakog okvira videa znatno sporije nego uobičajeno. Kada se "
"reproducira normalnom brzinom, vrijeme izgleda kao da prolazi brže. Montažni "
"program to postiže ubrzavanjem ili povećanjem brzine videa."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:444
msgid "Timeline:"
msgstr "Vremenska linija:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:445
msgid ""
"The Timeline is an editing interface that lays out a video project in a "
"linear fashion consisting of clips laid horizontally across the screen."
msgstr ""
"Vremenska linija je sučelje za montažu koje prikazuje video projekt "
"linearno, s isječcima postavljenim horizontalno preko zaslona."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:446
msgid "Timeline Editing:"
msgstr "Montaža na vremenskoj liniji:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:447
msgid ""
"Timeline editing is a computer-based method of editing, in which bars "
"proportional to the length of a clip, represent video and audio clips on a "
"computer screen."
msgstr ""
"Montaža na vremenskoj liniji je računalna metoda montaže u kojoj trake "
"proporcionalne duljini isječka predstavljaju video i audio isječke na "
"zaslonu računala."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:448
msgid "Titling:"
msgstr "Naslavljanje:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:449
msgid ""
"Titling is the process or result of incorporating on-screen text as credits, "
"captions, or any other alphanumeric communication."
msgstr ""
"Naslavljanje je proces ili rezultat uključivanja teksta na zaslonu kao "
"kredita, titlova ili bilo koje druge alfanumeričke komunikacije."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:450
msgid "Track:"
msgstr "Traka:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:451
msgid "A separate audio or video layer on a timeline."
msgstr "Poseban audio ili video sloj na vremenskoj liniji."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:452
msgid "Transcode:"
msgstr "Transkodiranje:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:453
msgid ""
"Converting a digital file to another digital file format.  This usually "
"involves audio and video compression."
msgstr ""
"Pretvaranje digitalne datoteke u drugi digitalni format. Obično uključuje "
"audio i video kompresiju."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:454
msgid "Transparency:"
msgstr "Prozirnost:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:455
msgid "Percentage of the opacity of a video clip or element."
msgstr "Postotak neprozirnosti video isječka ili elementa."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:456
msgid "Transition:"
msgstr "Prijelaz:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:457
msgid ""
"A method of juxtaposing two scenes.  Transitions can take many forms, "
"including cuts, dissolves, and wipes."
msgstr ""
"Metoda spajanja dviju scena. Prijelazi mogu imati različite oblike, "
"uključujući rezove, otapanja i brisanja."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:459
msgid "Trim:"
msgstr "Skraćivanje:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:459
msgid "Removing frames from the beginning, middle, or end of a clip."
msgstr "Uklanjanje okvira s početka, sredine ili kraja isječka."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:464
msgid "-V-"
msgstr "-V-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:465
msgid "Video Format:"
msgstr "Video format:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:466
msgid ""
"The video format is a standard that determines the way a video signal "
"records on videotape.  Standards include DV, 8-mm, Beta, and VHS."
msgstr ""
"Video format je standard koji određuje način snimanja video signala na "
"videokasetu. Standardi uključuju DV, 8-mm, Beta i VHS."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:467
msgid "Voiceover:"
msgstr "Naracija:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:468
msgid ""
"A term used to describe off-camera narration that is not part of a scene "
"(non-diegetic)."
msgstr ""
"Pojam koji opisuje naraciju izvan kamere koja nije dio scene (nedižetička)."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:470
msgid "VTR:"
msgstr "VTR:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:470
msgid ""
"A Videotape recorder also referred to as a 'deck'.  Decks duplicate "
"videotapes and inputting and outputting from a computer."
msgstr ""
"Snimatelj videokaseta, također nazvan 'deck'. Deckovi dupliciraju "
"videokasete te omogućuju unos i izlaz s računala."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:475
msgid "-W-"
msgstr "-W-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:476
msgid "Widescreen:"
msgstr "Široki zaslon:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:477
msgid ""
"A format in which the width-to-height ratio of the frame is greater than 4:3 "
"so that it is significantly wider than it is tall."
msgstr ""
"Format u kojem je omjer širine i visine kadra veći od 4:3, tako da je "
"značajno širi nego visok."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:479
msgid "Wipe:"
msgstr "Brisanje:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:479
msgid ""
"A wipe is a transition from one shot to another.  The edge of the transition "
"moves across the original image as a line or a pattern, revealing the new "
"shot."
msgstr ""
"Brisanje je prijelaz s jednog kadra na drugi. Rub prijelaza pomiče se preko "
"originalne slike kao linija ili uzorak, otkrivajući novi kadar."

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:484
msgid "-Z-"
msgstr "-Z-"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:486
msgid "Zoom:"
msgstr "Zum:"

# Translated with gpt-4.1-mini
#: ../glossary.rst:486
msgid ""
"A shot where the image grows more substantial or smaller by adjusting the "
"focal length of the lens instead of physically moving the camera."
msgstr ""
"Kadar u kojem slika postaje veća ili manja podešavanjem žarišne duljine "
"objektiva, umjesto fizičkog pomicanja kamere."
